WEBVTT

00:03:57.011 --> 00:04:00.551
who hatched elaborate plots,
maneuvered those around him,

00:04:00.551 --> 00:04:05.501
and cast a spell over characters
and audience alike.

00:04:05.501 --> 00:04:09.256
But by the end of his grand performance
of power and control,

00:04:09.256 --> 00:04:12.942
Prospero’s final lines see him humbled
by his audience -

00:04:12.942 --> 00:04:16.712
and the power
that they hold over his creations.

00:04:16.712 --> 00:04:20.602
"With the help of your good hands./
Gentle breath of yours my sails/

00:04:20.602 --> 00:04:26.292
Must fill or else my project fails,/
Which was to please."

00:04:26.292 --> 00:04:30.042
This evokes Shakespeare’s own role
as the great entertainer